1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The problem of finding edge-disjoint paths is a classic problem in graph theory and combinatorics, which falls under the purview of discrete mathematics. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents algorithms and complexity results for the Edge Disjoint Paths problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph algorithms and data structures. 
3. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper uses graph cuts and treecut width, which are concepts from computational geometry, to derive new results for the Edge Disjoint Paths problem. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The Edge Disjoint Paths problem has applications in game theory, where it can be used to model the connectivity of players in a game. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the computational complexity of the Edge Disjoint Paths problem and presents new results for the problem on different graph classes, which falls under the purview of computational complexity theory.
